                            <comment id="16513705" author="emilles" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2018 11:47:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is what I came up with for a fix in the transform class:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (Parameter fromParam : fromParams) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (hasAnnotation(fromParam, NAMED_PARAM_TYPE)) {
                    AnnotationNode namedParam = fromParam.getAnnotations(NAMED_PARAM_TYPE).get(0);
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; required = memberHasValue(namedParam, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;required&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Boolean&lt;/span&gt;.TRUE);
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// GRECLIPSE edit -- GROOVY-8627
&lt;/span&gt;                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (getMemberValue(namedParam, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (getMemberValue(namedParam, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;value&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// GRECLIPSE end
&lt;/span&gt;                        namedParam.addMember(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;value&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, constX(fromParam.getName()));
                    }
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name = getMemberStringValue(namedParam, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;value&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The annotation could be fixed by adding &quot;default null&quot; to the value attribute.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16514644" author="paulk" created="Sat, 16 Jun 2018 03:00:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The name vs value looks like a typo to me (I think I renamed the attribute from name to value but didn&apos;t fix this reference) and we didn&apos;t have test coverage for that case. The default value requirement looks appropriate too. Groovy is a bit more lax about checking that in some cases but better to be strict here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
